modules.description: Provides functions to parse and validate JSON strings, extract nested values, and convert between OCaml records and JSON representations. Operates on strings, JSON values, and OCaml variants with custom serialization rules. Used to process API responses and configuration files with structured data.

Provides a set of aliases for Owl modules to streamline access to core numerical computing components. Exposes types such as matrices, arrays, and tensors along with operations for linear algebra, statistical functions, and numerical computations. Enables tasks like matrix inversion, element-wise operations, and probability distribution sampling. Simplifies integration with Jupyter notebooks by offering direct access to key Owl functionalities.

This module offers functions for configuring and generating 2D/3D visualizations, including line plots, histograms, scatter plots, and surface charts, with support for custom styling via color, line style, and annotations. It operates on row-based matrices, vectors, and dense matrices (`dsmat`), enabling precise control over axes, legends, and scaling parameters. Use cases include statistical data analysis, numerical simulations, and scientific reporting, where detailed graphical representation of multidimensional datasets is required.
